      "writtenOn": "2020-04-01T00:00:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIU this will spin very very fast burning CPU. This isn\u0027t how Go code is written typically.\n\nI think we just need a loop like this\n\n  for {\n    select {\n     // case on context cancelation. exit.\n     // case on receiving an item.\n    }\n    // process the item\n  }\n\nthen we don\u0027t definitely don\u0027t need wg",
      "revId": "7380bf4f7f3abc34611f180db025d5c8f8f67a9d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
