    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7931e0e7_6751d5e4",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/gs_channel.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-01T01:21:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What about use of sync.Once?\n\ne.g.,\nhttps://golang.org/src/net/http/server.go?s\u003d96538:96593#L3324\n\n```\n// onceCloseListener wraps a net.Listener, protecting it from\n// multiple Close calls.\ntype onceCloseListener struct {\n\tnet.Listener\n\tonce     sync.Once\n\tcloseErr error\n}\n\nfunc (oc *onceCloseListener) Close() error {\n\toc.once.Do(oc.close)\n\treturn oc.closeErr\n}\n\nfunc (oc *onceCloseListener) close() { oc.closeErr \u003d oc.Listener.Close() }\n```\n\nIf it also looks an overkill, then I am happy to remove this code and let it panic on multiple close calls. Please let me know your opinion.",
      "parentUuid": "ed16a3e0_e18e0fa3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "7380bf4f7f3abc34611f180db025d5c8f8f67a9d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
