    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fc885ce5_a4d50578",
        "filename": "resultdb/sink/gs_channel.go",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 103,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-01T01:21:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "All of closeAndDrain(), close(), and uploadArtifact() are invoked by the user of this channel.\n\n\u003e\u003e Normally sending and closing is done by the same piece of code, to guarantee that we don\u0027t attempt to send after closure\nI believe that you are describing about such a module that internally sends data to and close an internal channel. This is not such a module.\n\nIt\u0027s normal that a class, struct, module provides reads, writes, and close functions.\ngsChannel provides uploadArtifact(), close(), and closeAndDrain() to its users.\n\nWould you want this module to maintain its terminate status, such that invocation of uploadArtifact() returns an error, such as ChannelClosed, after a call to close(), just like net/http.ErrServerClosed?\n \nhttps://golang.org/src/net/http/server.go?s\u003d96538:96593#L3074\n\n// ErrServerClosed is returned by the Server\u0027s Serve, ServeTLS, ListenAndServe,\n// and ListenAndServeTLS methods after a call to Shutdown or Close.\nvar ErrServerClosed \u003d errors.New(\"http: Server closed\")",
      "parentUuid": "64539bd5_1bb7731d",
      "revId": "7380bf4f7f3abc34611f180db025d5c8f8f67a9d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
